-- Greece’s New Democracy Leads Opposition Syriza Party, Poll Shows
-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 2013-06-27T10:05:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-27/greece-s-new-democracy-leads-opposition-syriza-party-poll-shows.html
PM Antonis Samaras’s New Democracy
party leads with 28.1% support of likely voters,  MRB poll  for
Real News showed.
*Opposition Syriza party at 26.6%
*Samaras’s coalition partner Pasok has 7.8%
*Nationalist  Golden Dawn  placed third with 11.6%
*Former coalition partner Democratic Left at 3.8%
*80.3% of those polled say things in the country going badly
*26.4% say new coalition govt. as bad as previous govt, 30% say
new govt is worse
*52.4% believe govt won’t finish term, 53.3% want govt to finish
term
*MRB surveyed 1,014 people June 25, margin of error +/-2.5%
*NOTE: Next Greek parliamentary elections scheduled in 2016
*NOTE: Greek Coalition Government Stability Shaken as Party
